      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 2.863,
      "end": 5.584,
      "text": "All Libra-Vox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.264,
      "end": 12.225,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit librivox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 13.685,
      "end": 14.786,
      "text": "Aesip's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 15.786,
      "end": 17.566,
      "text": "The North Wind and the Sun.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 19.586,
      "end": 25.427,
      "text": "A dispute arose between the North Wind and the Sun, each claiming that he was stronger than the other.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 26.328,
      "end": 29.108,
      "text": "At last they agreed to try their powers upon a traveler.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 29.673,
      "end": 32.196,
      "text": "to see which could soon strip him of his cloak.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 33.177,
      "end": 46.672,
      "text": "The Northwind had the first try, and gathering up all his force for the attack, he came whirling furiously down upon the man, and caught up his cloak as though he would rest it from him by one single effort.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 47.588,
      "end": 51.469,
      "text": "But the harder he blew, the more closely the man wrapped it round himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 52.049,
      "end": 53.589,
      "text": "Then came the turn of the sun.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 54.23,
      "end": 61.371,
      "text": "At first he beamed gently upon the traveler, who soon unclassed his cloak, and walked on with it hanging loosely about his shoulders.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 62.311,
      "end": 71.834,
      "text": "Then he shone forth in his full strength, and the man, before he had gone many steps, was glad to throw his cloak right off and complete his journey more lightly clad.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 72.834,
      "end": 74.994,
      "text": "Persuasion is better than force.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 76.015,
      "end": 77.355,
      "text": "End of the North Wind",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 77.976,
      "end": 78.541,
      "text": "and the sun.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
